{'istart': 1, 'iend': 23, 'talk': 'It should not be done,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 43, 'talk': 'Then when may I expect to get my Jingzhou?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 59, 'talk': 'As Lu Su invites me, I will come tomorrow; you may return,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 61, 'iend': 120, 'talk': 'Why did you promise to go? I think Lu Su means you no good.', 'context': 'After the messenger had gone, Guan Ping said to his father, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 315, 'talk': 'Do you think I do not know? This has all come out of my refusal to yield those three territories. They are going to try coercion at this banquet. If I refuse, they will think I fear them. I will go tomorrow in a small ship with just my ten personal guards, and we shall see whether Lu Su will dare to come near me.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 318, 'iend': 451, 'talk': "But, Father, why risk your priceless self in the very den of a tiger? I think you are not giving due importance to my uncle's charge.", 'context': ' “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 215, 'talk': 'I have been in the midst of million blades and arrows, yet I have been riding through all directions like traveling through a meadow of no one; think you that I shall begin to show fear of a few such rats as those?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 139, 'talk': 'Although Lu Su has a great repute, yet now he is pushed hard. He certainly is badly disposed toward you, and you must be careful, General.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 18, 'iend': 412, 'talk': 'I have given my word, and shall I withdraw from it? In the days of the Warring States, Liu Xiangru of the state of Zhao had not the force even to bind a chicken, yet in the assembly at Shengchi Lake he regarded not the prince and the ministers of the powerful state of Qin, but did his duty without fear of consequences. Have I not learned to face any number of foes? I cannot break my promise.', 'context': 'Guan Yu replied, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 16, 'talk': 'If you must go,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 34, 'iend': 55, 'talk': 'at least go prepared.', 'context': ' said Ma Liang, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 177, 'talk': 'Tell my son to choose out ten fast ships and five hundred of good marines and be in readiness to help me at need. And when he sees a red flag waved, he can come over to my aid.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 27, 'talk': 'What do you think of this?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 230, 'talk': 'If Guan Yu comes with a force, Gan Ning and I will be in readiness for him by the river−side. And you will hear our bomb as a signal that we are attacking. If he has no force with him, the assassins can set on during the banquet.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 189, 'iend': 196, 'talk': 'Guan Yu', 'context': 'Next day a look−out was kept on the bank, and early in the day a single ship came along. It was manned by very few men, and a simple red flag flew out on the breeze showing but two words, “'},
{'istart': 52, 'iend': 388, 'talk': 'I have a word to say to you, Sir, if haply I may have your attention. You know that your illustrious brother, the Imperial Uncle, made me surety with my master that Jingzhou would be returned after Yiazhou had been taken. Well, now that country is in his possession, but Jingzhou is still unreturned. Is not this a breach of good faith?', 'context': 'When they had become mellow with wine, Lu Su said, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 29, 'talk': 'This is a government affair,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 46, 'iend': 97, 'talk': 'Such matters should not be introduced at a banquet.', 'context': ' said Guan Yu. “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 363, 'talk': 'My master only has petty possessions in the east, and he allowed the temporary loan of Jingzhou out of consideration for the need in which you then were. But now you have Yiazhou, and Jingzhou should be given up. The Imperial Uncle has even yielded three territories, but you, Sir, seem unwilling to let them go. This seems hard to explain on reasonable grounds.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 18, 'iend': 232, 'talk': 'My brother braved the arrows and the stones in the battle at Wuling and with all his strength drove back the enemy; did he get a single foot of land for all his efforts? Now you come to force this place out of him.', 'context': 'Guan Yu replied, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 14, 'talk': 'No; I do not,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 29, 'iend': 565, 'talk': 'But at the time that you and your brother suffered defeat at Dangyang, when you were helpless and in the greatest straits, fugitives you knew not whither, then my master was moved with pity and did not grudge the land. So he gave your brother a foothold whence he might be able to accomplish other ends. But your brother has presumed upon long−suffering. He has attained his end—the country of his desire—and still he occupies Jingzhou. Such greed and such treachery will make the whole world laugh him to shame, as you know quite well.', 'context': ' said Lu Su. “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 76, 'talk': "All that is no affair of mine; it is my brother's. I cannot yield the land.", 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 163, 'talk': 'I know that by the oath in the Peach Garden you three were to live or die together. But your brother has consented to yield; how are you going to get out of that?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 94, 'iend': 177, 'talk': 'Only the virtuous get hold of territory, does that mean only you people of East Wu?', 'context': 'Guan Yu was at a loss to reply. However, Zhou Cang burst into the conversation, roaring out, “'},
{'istart': 7, 'iend': 231, 'talk': 'You have kindly invited me today, Sir, but do not say anything about Jingzhou, for I am so drunk that I may forget our old friendship. Some other day I hope to invite you to Jingzhou, and then we will talk about that matter.', 'context': 'said, “'},
{'istart': 100, 'iend': 121, 'talk': 'What can be done now?', 'context': 'Guan Yu took his homeward way, while Lu Su and his two confederates talked over what had occurred. “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 63, 'talk': 'The only thing is to tell our master and let him send an army,', 'context': '“'},
