{'istart': 1, 'iend': 72, 'talk': 'Gentlemen, it seems you are selfish and not devoted to the common weal,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 92, 'iend': 225, 'talk': 'You may have your private reasons for what you do, but I intend to go out and try to repel the enemy. I will fight them to the death.', 'context': ' said Zhang Liao. “'},
{'istart': 128, 'iend': 249, 'talk': 'How can I be careless of the common weal and indulge my private feelings? I am ready to follow you and do as you command.', 'context': "Thereupon Zhang Liao bade his servants saddle his steed. At this, Li Dian's better feelings were aroused, and he rose, saying, “"},
{'istart': 56, 'iend': 299, 'talk': 'Since I can depend upon your help, my friend, then I would ask you to lie in ambush on the north of the Flageolet Ford in order to destroy the bridge there as soon as the army of Wu has crossed. I, with my friend Yue Jin, will smite the enemy.', 'context': 'Zhang Liao was elated at this moral victory, and said, “'},
