{'istart': 62, 'iend': 265, 'talk': 'About ten miles from the city there is the Pool of the Leaping Dragon. Near it is a shrine, and beside that grows a fine pear tree. It is over a hundred spans high, and that will serve for the roof tree.', 'context': ' said the architect. “'},
{'istart': 320, 'iend': 553, 'talk': 'Behold the Spirit of the Pear Tree. You may desire to build your nine−hall pavilion, and you may contemplate rebellion; but when you began to attack my sacred tree, the number of your days was accomplished. I am come now to slay you.', 'context': 'But that evening when he retired to rest, he could not sleep. He rose, went into the outer room, and sat there leaning on a low table. Suddenly a man appeared with his hair unbound, dressed in black and carrying a naked sword. The visitor came straight toward Cao Cao, stopped in front of him and, pointing, cried out, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 22, 'talk': 'Where are the guards?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 81, 'iend': 116, 'talk': 'My lord, have you heard of Hua Tuo?', 'context': "was universal among Cao Cao's subordinates. Hua Xin one day said to his master, “"},
{'istart': 119, 'iend': 162, 'talk': 'Do you mean him of Qiao who cured Zhou Tai?', 'context': ' “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 17, 'talk': 'Yes; that is he,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 87, 'talk': 'I have heard something of his fame, but I know nothing of his capabilities in his art.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 450, 'talk': "A dog bit a man's toe, and two tumorous growths ensued, one of which itched intolerably and the other pained severely. Hua Tuo said the painful one contained ten needles, and the other a couple of chess pips, black and white. He opened the two swellings, and the contents were as he had said. Really he is of the same class of physician as masters Bian Que and Zang Kong of old times. He lives at Jincheng, not far away, and could be here very soon.", 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 277, 'talk': 'Prince, your headaches are due to a malignant humor within the brain case. The humor is too thick to get out. Swallowing drugs will do no good. But I propose to administer a dose of hashish, then open the brain case and remove the thickened humor. That will be a radical cure.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 30, 'talk': 'You mean you want to kill me?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 191, 'talk': 'O Prince, you have heard how I cured Guan Yu of the poison that had got into his bones? I scraped them, and he did not hesitate a moment. Your malady is trifling, and why do you mistrust me?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 203, 'talk': "A painful arm may be scraped, but how can you cut open a man's head? The fact is you have conspired with some of Guan Yu's friends to take this opportunity to make away with me in revenge for his death.", 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 33, 'iend': 100, 'talk': 'The man possesses rare skills; to kill him is to waste his talents.', 'context': 'Jia Xu pleaded for him, saying, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 87, 'talk': 'The man wants to get a chance to kill me; he is the same sort of scoundrel as Ji Ping.', 'context': '“'},
