{'istart': 1, 'iend': 659, 'talk': 'But we are now in other times. Since there is not the state of confusion that waited on the end of Qin, but a state of things more nearly like that of the period of the Warring States, in which six kingdoms contended for the mastery, therefore one may play the part of King Wen. If one would found a dynasty, then must that one wait upon time and favorable destiny. With these in his favor, the consummation will follow forthwith, as the armies of Kings Tang and Wu fought but one battle. Therefore have real compassion for the people and wait on opportunity. If wars are constant, and a mishap come, even the wisest will be unable to show the way of safety.', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 45, 'talk': 'An effusion from the pen of a rotten pedant?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 39, 'talk': 'In your opinion where should we begin?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 18, 'iend': 275, 'talk': 'The great storehouse of Wei is at Changcheng, and we ought to burn their grain and forage. Let us go out by the Luo Valley and cross the Shen Ridge. After the capture of Changcheng, we can go on to Qinchuan, and the conquest of the Middle Land will be near.', 'context': 'Fu Qian replied, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 48, 'talk': 'What you say just fits in with my secret plans,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 52, 'iend': 361, 'talk': 'Sima Zhao has forced his prince to go with him to war, which plainly indicates that he intends to emulate the deeds of Li Jue and Guo Si. My government has commanded me to punish this fault. Wherefore I say to you yield at once; for if you persist in the way of error, you and yours shall all be put to death.', 'context': 'Jiang Wei stood in the front of his army and said, “'},
{'istart': 25, 'iend': 234, 'talk': "You and yours are wholly strangers to any feeling of rectitude. You have repeatedly invaded a superior state's territory; and if you do not at once retire, I will see to it that not even a breastplate returns.", 'context': 'Sima Wang shouted back, “'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 31, 'talk': 'Do you recognize General Deng?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 20, 'talk': 'So this is Deng Ai,', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 62, 'talk': 'If I cannot gain the advantage by some ruse, how shall I win?', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 1, 'iend': 32, 'talk': 'What a pity! What a great pity!', 'context': '“'},
{'istart': 18, 'iend': 85, 'talk': 'Jiang Wei, you fool, do not pursue my son when I, Deng Ai, am here!', 'context': 'front, shouting, “'},
{'istart': 9, 'iend': 285, 'talk': 'General, we should not give battle, but wait for reinforcements. Meanwhile the soldiers of Shu will be consuming their supply of grain, and we will attack on three sides when they begin to be hungry. I send my son Deng Zhong to you for further help in the defense of the city.', 'context': 'saying, “'},
